Key Match Events: The T20 World Cup match between South Africa and Zimbabwe was called off after multiple rain interruptions.
Zimbabwe posted 79 for five after the match was reduced to nine-over-a-side.
Wessly Madhevere scored 35 not out and Milton Shumba scored 18 for Zimbabwe.
Lungi Ngidi picked up two wickets for South Africa with figures of 2/20.
Quinton de Kock led South Africa’s chase with 47 not out off 18 balls.
The Proteas were 51 for no loss in 3 overs before rain ended the match.
Pre-Game Insights: South Africa aimed to start their T20 World Cup campaign on a high after losing the T20I series to India.
Zimbabwe reached the Super 12 by beating Ireland and Scotland in the group stage.
All eyes were on South Africa skipper Temba Bavuma, who was going through a lean patch with the bat.
David Miller and Rilee Rossouw were key players for South Africa in the middle order, while Quinton de Kock was expected to give a solid start at the top.
Sikandar Raza was highlighted as the key player for Zimbabwe due to his standout performances over the past year.
Post-Match Reflections: Rain denied South Africa a crucial win as both teams shared a point each.
Quinton de Kock expressed disappointment as South Africa were robbed of a win due to rain.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Group 2 clash was reduced to a 9-over-a-side match due to rain.
The start of the match was delayed due to rain in Hobart.
